search for installed and available **nuts**

@@SYNOPSYS:@@
##find## <options> [-js <JAVASCRIPT EXPRESSION>]  [ [-e] <LIKE EXPRESSION> ...]

searches for installed and available **nuts**. Found **nuts** are displayed as namespace aware **nuts** ids
(starting wth namespace:// where namespace is the name of the repository where the **nuts** was found).
When no expressions and no options are provided, all available **nuts** (in all registered repositories)
will be listed.

@@OPTIONS:@@
-i          : only installed **nuts** will be displayed.
-!i         : only non installed **nuts** will be displayed.
-u          : only updatable **nuts** will be displayed.
-!u         : only non updatable **nuts** will be displayed.
-o          : offline mode (no remote/http access)
-R          : remote mode (no local files)
-d          : display descriptor
-D          : display effective descriptor
-e          : shell like expressions are used for searching. (SLE) Shell Like Expression may continue * as wildcard.
              When using SLE expressions (with or without the -e option), multiple expressions are interpreted as an OR expression.
-js         : the filter expression is interpreted as javascript expression which MUST contain a return clause.
              The expression should filter against the predefined 'id' variable.
              When using both javascript and SLE expressions, an error will be thrown.

@@Find Expressions:@@
-x    --expression        : non js expression
-p    --pkg   <PKG>         : accept packagings
-a    --arch  <ARCH>        : accept architectures ("x86", "ia64", "amd64", "ppc", "sparc")
-r    --repo  <REPO>        : accept only listed repository
-e    --exec              : accept executable **nuts**
-!e   --lib               : accept non executable (libs) **nuts**
-u    --updatable         : accept updatable **nuts**
-!u   --non-updatable     : accept non updatable **nuts**
-i    --installed         : accept installed **nuts**
-!i   --non-installed     : accept non installed **nuts**
-v    --last-version      : accept latest versions only


@@Fetch Mode:@@
-F    --offline           : search in local repos only
-O    --online            : search in local and remote repos
-R    --remote            : search in remote repos only
-M    --commitable        : search for **nuts** that are newer than remote
-U    --updatable         : search for **nuts** that are older than remote
-T    --status            : search for **nuts** that are newer or older than remote


-l    --long              : display long format

-f    --file              : display **nuts** file path
-c    --class             : display **nuts** Main class
-s    --descriptor        : display **nuts** descriptor
-b    --effective-descriptor
                          : display **nuts** effective descriptor
-g    --installed-dependencies
                          : display **nuts** installed dependencies
-d    --dependencies      : display **nuts** all dependencies


-I    --display-id        : (default) display **nuts** ids
-N    --display-name      : display **nuts** name
-P    --display-packaging : display packaging instead of ids
-A    --display-arch      : display architectures instead of ids
-L    --display-file      : display files instead of ids
-C    --display-class     : display classes instead of ids
-Y    --summary           : display a summary line with list count and perf stats


-h -? --help              : show this help

@@EXAMPLES:@@

##find##
   searches for and displays ALL available **nuts**

##find## -i
   searches for and displays ALL installed **nuts**

##find## -i \"ab*\" \"*yz\"
   searches for and displays installed **nuts** that starts with 'ab' or ends with 'yz'

##find## -e \"ab*\"
   searches for and displays executable **nuts** that starts with 'ab'

##find## -js \"return id.version.ge(\'1.2\') && id.version.le(\'1.8\')\"
   searches for and displays installed **nuts** with version between 1.2 and 1.8 (exclusively)

##find## -r vpc-public-nuts -R net.vpc.app:nuts net.vpc.app.nuts:nuts-core
   searches for and displays remote (will not look locally) at the vpc-public-nuts repository for newest versions of nuts and nuts-core
